net.sf.mmm.orient.data.bean.api.audio

Interface AudioTrack

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AbstractMedia, AbstractName, AbstractTrack, Bean, Entity, EntityBean, OrientBean, Vertex

    public interface AudioTrack
extends AbstractTrack
    This is the OrientBean for an audio track. It represents the metadata of a single audio record such as a song, a chapter of an audio-book, etc. Any single audio file (ogg, mp3, flac, etc.) or any single track on an audio CD corresponds to an AudioTrack.
    Typically an AudioTrack belongs to an AudioAlbum that groups the tracks belonging together (e.g. to an audio CD).
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    hohwille

      • Bpm

      • Genre

      • CoverOf

        LinkProperty<AudioTrack> CoverOf()

      • MusicalKey

        StringProperty MusicalKey()
        Returns:
        the musical key of the track. Value will be empty if no music, not in a main key, or unknown.

      • PrimaryLanguage

        LinkProperty<Language> PrimaryLanguage()
        Returns:
        the primary Language of the track. Value will be empty if undefined, or if in no language (e.g. instrumantal).

      • AdditionalLanguages

        LinkListProperty<Language> AdditionalLanguages()
        Returns:
        the list of optional additional Languages of the track. Sometimes a song has verses in different languages or the refrain is in a different language. In that case all Languages in addition to the primary language should be listed here.

      • Artist

      • Composer

        LinkProperty<AbstractArtist> Composer()
        Returns:
        the optional artist who composed this track. Should only be set if different from Artist().
